      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Substantive due process is a vital constitutional safeguard that protects fundamental individual liberties from government overreach. It ensures that the government cannot infringe upon core rights, even if it follows proper legal procedures. This doctrine has been instrumental in expanding civil rights by striking down laws that violate deeply held personal freedoms. It is a cornerstone of protecting individual autonomy against state power.",
